    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix IPv4 address validation rejecting valid addresses including 0.0.0.0\n\n### Summary\nThe config_assign_ipv4addr function was incorrectly rejecting valid IPv4 addresses, particularly \"0.0.0.0\" (INADDR_ANY), due to flawed validation logic that checked if the converted address was greater than 0. This caused configuration failures when trying to bind services to all interfaces.\n\nThis fix corrects the validation to accept any valid IPv4 address that inet_pton successfully converts.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/config/config_common.c`: Modified config_assign_ipv4addr to only check inet_pton return value rather than converted address value\n- Removed unreachable return statement\n- Preserved special handling for ANY_IPV4ADDR_STRING (\"0.0.0.0\")\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure any network service to bind to \"0.0.0.0\" \n2. Start the OAI application\n3. Observe configuration failure with error message \"[CONFIG] 0.0.0.0 not valid for <parameter_name>\"\n4. Application fails to start or binds to incorrect interface\n\nThe fix ensures that \"0.0.0.0\" and other valid IPv4 addresses are properly accepted during configuration.\n"
}